    "summary": "Yes — \"traditional metaphysics\" main + \"pre-nihilist\" TN works",
    "content": "Yes, this works well. It is arguably better than my proposal.\n\n\"Traditional metaphysics\" is what the reader already expects -- it is a phrase with an established meaning in English philosophy (roughly: the metaphysical tradition from Parmenides through Hegel that nihilism disrupted). The reader does not stumble on it. The TN then sharpens the meaning: \"traditional\" here means specifically \"pre-nihilist,\" i.e., the dividing line is the nihilistic crisis, not Kant's critique, not the linguistic turn, not Habermas's intersubjective turn.\n\nThe only thing I would add to the TN is the author's own words: \"是我创造出来的一个名词\" -- \"this is a term I coined.\" This signals to the reader that 前形而上学 / \"traditional metaphysics\" is the author's own category, not an inherited label from the secondary literature. One sentence does the job."
  }
}
